Day 8: SQL – Aggregate Functions & GROUP BY

Topic:
SQL Aggregate Functions and GROUP BY Clause

Learning Objectives:

Understand aggregate functions such as COUNT, SUM, AVG, MIN, and MAX
Learn how to group records using GROUP BY
Understand the purpose of the HAVING clause
Learn the difference between WHERE and HAVING conditions
Analyze and summarize data using SQL queries

Activities / Deliverables:

Create a sales summary report using aggregate functions
Calculate totals, averages, minimum, and maximum values from sample data
Group records based on categories or departments
Filter grouped results using the HAVING clause
Practice combining GROUP BY with aggregate functions in queries

Tools / Tech:

MySQL 8

